The Ragpicker seems content to watch you search through the belongings of your fallen comrades. She hugs herself in the cold air, apparently too weary from her previous efforts to join you.
This elegant ring bears the warm glow of true gold. It looks like it belongs on the hand of a courtier or noble.

Small figures, crudely cut, dance chaotically around the ring's circumference. You doubt the ring would fetch more than a few coppers from a merchant but something tells you that it holds a greater significance. You seem to remember it from an earlier time. Perhaps you wore one like it once or saw it on another's hand.

This bloodstained battleaxe seems solidly crafted and the inlaid gold seems genuine. Etched into the heavy blade is a single word: "Witchbane."
The sun-bleached corpse groans and shifts, a gust of wind giving it the brief appearance of unlife.
Place this object in any area where you want tracking to occur.  Set Will to the DC of tracking in this area.
